Size()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may not be the effect you want."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can think of ","type":"text"},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as the creation of a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"counter proposal"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view, and the specific effects of ","type":"text"},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" depends on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"particular view and how you have configured it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"vertical dimensions, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/foreach\/fixedsize()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ForEach":{"abstract":[{"text":"A structure that computes views on demand from an underlying collection of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"identified data.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ForEach","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ForEach","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ForEach","identifi